<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb5c720c9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s290kk–2"><num value="290kk–2">§ 290kk–2.</num><heading> Limitations on use of funds for certain purposes</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No funds provided under a designated program shall be expended for sectarian worship, instruction, or proselytization.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb5c720ca-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373">July 1, 1944, ch. 373</ref>, title V, § 596B, formerly § 583, as added <ref href="/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/7/tI/s144">Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(7) [title I, § 144]</ref>, <date date="2000-12-21">Dec. 21, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2763">114 Stat. 2763</ref>, 2763A–622; renumbered § 596B, <ref href="/us/pl/119/44/tI/s107/a/2">Pub. L. 119–44, title I, § 107(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="2025-12-01">Dec. 1, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/674">139 Stat. 674</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
